description:
Fully unlocked, MWO-style Mechlab, with all missing MWO Mech variants and weapon and AMS hardpoints. Supports vanilla savegames and mech mods. Coop compatible.

0.52

All vanilla game savegames and mechs / loadouts will be upgraded with new Slots and equipment (Engines, Endo, Ferro etc).
Tanks, VTOLs and Turrets have increased HP (scalable Mod Option setting).

Mech Abilities (with configurable keybinds now):
Consumables (need equipment):
Cool Shot
UAV
Extras:
Thermal Vision
Headlights
Bullet-Time

Key binds for the above can be set in the Options menu now (Controls - scroll to the bottom).

No friendly fire, UAV auto-launch and rescale config (and more) in Game.ini (%localappdata% / MW5Mercs / Saved / Config / WindowsNoEditor) - compatible with Bobbert's Mod Options mod (adds a Mod Options tab to Options menu to have proper GUI for various mod's configurable variables):
https://www.nexusmods.com/mechwarrior5mercenaries/mods/537

More info on the Nexus page about compatibility and known bugs:
https://www.nexusmods.com/mechwarrior5mercenaries/mods/459

Please go there and read the description and possibly the comments.

This is NOT compatible with many other mods. List of known compatible and incompatible mods is on Nexus. It the mod has "YAML" in its name, it should work.

Includes @trueg's code for advanced equipment properties, config file and a lot more.

https://github.com/mw5mercs-modding/yaml-docs

Trueg's mods:
https://www.nexusmods.com/mechwarrior5mercenaries/users/37353075
https://steamcommunity.com/id/truegerich/myworkshopfiles/

YAML Discord:
https://discord.gg/SnVahkkHEn

Item lists:
https://github.com/mw5mercs-modding/yaml-docs
